<grammar>
<section>
<title>Use of articles  </title>
<sectiontitle>We use zero article (no article) + plural or uncountable noun to talk about things in general.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_11_3_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1>with a plural noun</text1>
<text1a>Jane loves &lt;b&gt;cats&lt;/b&gt;.</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_11_3_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2>with an uncountable noun</text2>
<text2a>&lt;b&gt;Meat&lt;/b&gt; is good for you.</text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_11_3_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>We use &lt;i&gt;a/an&lt;/i&gt; + a singular noun to talk about things for the first time or when we don't know which one. </sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>el_gram_11_3_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3></text3>
<text3a>Have you got &lt;b&gt;a pen&lt;/b&gt;?</text3a>
<sound3>el_gram_11_3_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4></text4>
<text4a>We live in &lt;b&gt;a small flat&lt;/b&gt;.</text4a>
<sound4>el_gram_11_3_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
<section>
<title>Use of articles</title>
<sectiontitle>We use &lt;i&gt;the&lt;/i&gt; + noun to talk about specific things or when we already know which one.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_11_3_7.mp3</titlesound>
<text1>We stayed in a hotel in Bangkok.</text1>
<text1a>Was &lt;b&gt;the hotel&lt;/b&gt; good?</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_11_3_8.mp3</sound1>
<text2>Are you cold?</text2>
<text2a>Yes, can I close &lt;b&gt;the window&lt;/b&gt;?</text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_11_3_9.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2></sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2></titlesound2>
